Generate Scaled data

Source: R/util.R
scale_data.Rd

This function generates a scaled data.

Usage

scale_data(data, weights, global_val)

Arguments

data

A matrix representing the data which needed to be scaled.

weights

A numeric vector containing weights for each dimensions.

global_val

A numeric list containing global minimum and maximum.

Value

A scaled data.

Examples

set.seed(20240412)
data1 <- gen_gaussian(n= 500, p = 4)
#> âœ” Data generation completed successfully! ğŸ‰
data2 <- gen_bluntedcorn(n= 300, p = 4)
#> âœ” Data generation completed successfully! ğŸ‰
dfs <- list(data1, data2)
global_minmax <- gen_globalminmax(data_list = dfs, p = 4)
scale_data(data = data2, weights = c(1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 0.5),
global_val = global_minmax)
